The paper discusses the design and implementation of a synchronization protocol for intermittently powered wireless embedded systems, specifically the WISP platform. This involves coordination and collaboration among individual WISPs, which suggests a focus on multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of RFID technology and wireless communication also points towards networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the need for synchronization in complex applications, which could involve robotics (cs.RO) or control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with energy-efficient systems, which could fall under the category of embedded systems (cs.EM).
